02:09.939 --> 02:12.156
(Grunts softly)

02:19.817 --> 02:22.367
Were you watching me sleep?

02:22.369 --> 02:24.453
Hmm.

02:24.455 --> 02:25.838
Possibly...

02:27.435 --> 02:29.007
a little.

02:41.438 --> 02:45.696
Despite everything that we've done...

02:45.726 --> 02:49.561
all those we've lost...

02:49.563 --> 02:53.515
we're still here.

02:53.517 --> 02:55.650
You're not alone.

03:06.030 --> 03:08.285
What better life might have awaited you

03:08.315 --> 03:11.533
were another man your father?

03:11.635 --> 03:16.443
All those who have loved
me have lived to regret it.

03:16.954 --> 03:21.226
But I do know this, my littlest wolf.

03:21.558 --> 03:24.396
I will do right by you.

03:26.487 --> 03:28.506
(Footsteps approaching)

03:28.536 --> 03:31.070
What do you want, Elijah?

03:36.540 --> 03:38.577
I'm not foolish enough
to ask your forgiveness,

03:38.579 --> 03:40.245
so I'll say it again.

03:40.667 --> 03:43.415
I had no choice.

03:43.617 --> 03:47.669
We protect this family at any cost.

03:48.789 --> 03:51.957
You think I'm not aware of
how heavy that burden is?

03:52.304 --> 03:54.910
No. I think that this time,

03:54.912 --> 03:58.163
that burden...

03:58.165 --> 04:00.666
is simply too much to bear.

04:13.196 --> 04:15.431
Something isn't right.

04:15.433 --> 04:17.516
Well, you said you put
the prophecy to rest.

04:17.974 --> 04:19.184
So what's the worry?

04:19.653 --> 04:21.437
I didn't sleep last night.

04:21.738 --> 04:24.072
I just had this feeling of dread.

04:24.074 --> 04:25.846
I don't know if it's my own guilt,

04:25.876 --> 04:28.927
or maybe it's my intuition
telling me something's coming.

04:30.588 --> 04:31.980
And what's this?

04:31.982 --> 04:34.849
Your early warning system?

04:35.151 --> 04:36.723
This map is spelled to trace

04:36.753 --> 04:38.568
Niklaus's enemies.

04:39.022 --> 04:41.823
Let's just hope I'm being paranoid.

04:43.091 --> 04:44.114
(Sighs)

04:44.144 --> 04:47.062
(Reciting incantation)

05:03.697 --> 05:05.447
I guess you're not being paranoid

05:05.477 --> 05:06.504
when there is, in fact,

05:06.534 --> 05:08.834
a hoard of killers out to get you.

05:19.680 --> 05:20.918
All this was you?

05:20.948 --> 05:23.654
No. I had help.

05:23.684 --> 05:24.605
Davina Claire.

05:24.635 --> 05:25.884
She's the one that
made sure the Ancestors

05:25.886 --> 05:26.969
were gone for good.

05:28.173 --> 05:29.610
It's the last thing she did.

05:29.640 --> 05:30.828
That means you've done your part.

05:30.858 --> 05:32.558
That just leaves me to do mine.

05:32.560 --> 05:34.643
Are you sure you can?

05:35.475 --> 05:37.368
Am I sure I can?

05:37.753 --> 05:39.370
The whole point of me
taking Lucien's serum

05:39.400 --> 05:41.400
was so I'd have the power
to deal with the Mikaelsons.

05:41.430 --> 05:44.153
Marcel, there's a big difference
between having the power

05:44.155 --> 05:46.071
and actually using the
power to kill somebody.

05:46.073 --> 05:47.406
And these people were your family.

05:47.408 --> 05:49.542
They were my family.

05:49.868 --> 05:51.243
Do you know why I even
bothered pretending

05:51.245 --> 05:53.349
like I hadn't already taken the serum?

05:53.496 --> 05:56.782
I needed to see how
my family would react.

05:56.784 --> 05:59.201
Elijah killed me in cold blood.

06:01.021 --> 06:02.604
Yeah.

06:02.606 --> 06:04.356
So whatever happens
next, they've earned it.

06:04.358 --> 06:06.191
Did the people of New
Orleans earn it, too?

06:06.193 --> 06:08.360
'Cause I've been hearing
the rumors about vampires

06:08.362 --> 06:10.112
just flocking into
town, and it looks to me

06:10.114 --> 06:11.864
like you're dead set on starting a war.

06:11.866 --> 06:13.949
And I need to know what
happens to the innocent people

06:13.951 --> 06:16.201
when they get caught in
the crossfire of that.

06:16.203 --> 06:17.836
No. You got to promise me

06:17.838 --> 06:20.539
you're gonna do what's right
for the people of this city.

06:21.532 --> 06:24.560
That's exactly what I'm gonna do.

06:29.357 --> 06:30.565
Freya's tracking

06:30.595 --> 06:32.067
your sirelings now.

06:32.069 --> 06:33.401
So it won't be long.

06:33.403 --> 06:34.619
Which works for me.

06:34.621 --> 06:36.289
I could use a good fight.

06:36.863 --> 06:39.624
Well, we do have an advantage.

06:40.293 --> 06:41.272
No vampire may enter

06:41.302 --> 06:42.782
this stronghold so long as the deed

06:42.812 --> 06:44.451
remains in Freya's name.

06:44.481 --> 06:45.714
So what?

06:45.744 --> 06:48.467
We hide in here while our
enemies mass at the front gate?

06:48.497 --> 06:50.052
Well, if they're so
determined to die at our hands,

06:50.054 --> 06:51.053
let them come.

06:51.055 --> 06:53.255
(Freya reciting incantation)

07:06.229 --> 07:07.229
No.

07:07.941 --> 07:09.688
(Whooshing, Freya gasps)

07:14.579 --> 07:16.745
(Crowd murmuring nearby)

07:20.034 --> 07:22.618
(Footsteps approaching)

07:41.070 --> 07:43.621
MARCEL: Never thought
it would come to this.

07:43.651 --> 07:47.491
But, as always...

07:48.016 --> 07:52.013
the Mikaelsons made my choice for me.

07:52.365 --> 07:53.921
Marcel.

07:53.951 --> 07:55.105
How?

07:55.135 --> 07:57.886
How are we in your home?

07:59.123 --> 08:01.061
I have friends who can nullify a deed,

08:01.091 --> 08:02.925
- foreclose on a property like that.
- (Snaps fingers)

08:02.927 --> 08:05.002
Or did you mean...

08:05.441 --> 08:08.263
how am I not a rotting corpse?

08:12.170 --> 08:14.436
I thought my friend was dead,

08:14.438 --> 08:16.521
and yet here you are.

08:16.523 --> 08:18.190
So send these fools away,

08:18.192 --> 08:20.275
and let's talk.

08:20.527 --> 08:21.643
You and me.

08:21.645 --> 08:23.812
Is that relief I hear?

08:24.239 --> 08:25.497
Really?

08:25.527 --> 08:27.632
If I hadn't been one step ahead of you,

08:27.634 --> 08:30.024
I would be at the bottom of the river.

08:30.054 --> 08:30.545
ELIJAH: Marcel,

08:30.575 --> 08:32.498
your anger is with me.

08:33.934 --> 08:36.357
I am the one that's responsible
for this crime against you.

08:36.359 --> 08:40.100
One thing I learned sticking
around this family, Elijah,

08:40.130 --> 08:41.501
you take on one of you,

08:41.530 --> 08:43.365
you are taking on all of you.

08:43.857 --> 08:45.283
These guys,

08:45.285 --> 08:49.204
Klaus's sirelings, they're
here to bear witness today.

08:49.206 --> 08:53.091
Are you planning to put on
a little show, Marcellus?

08:53.093 --> 08:55.644
Damned sure that I am.

08:55.674 --> 08:58.230
The fall of the Mikaelsons.

08:58.788 --> 09:00.232
And guess what.

09:01.396 --> 09:03.578
The show has already started.

09:10.770 --> 09:13.234
(Crowd clamoring)

09:13.264 --> 09:14.507
You're gonna have to listen to me now.

09:14.537 --> 09:15.836
You're gonna have to hear me out,

09:15.838 --> 09:17.788
because I understand
what you're going through.

09:17.790 --> 09:19.206
Our connection with the Ancestors

09:19.208 --> 09:20.624
has been severed; it's gone.

09:20.626 --> 09:22.209
What about the vampires?

09:22.239 --> 09:24.857
- (Crowd murmurs agreement)
- Their numbers increase by the hour

09:24.887 --> 09:26.547
while our strength has diminished.

09:26.549 --> 09:28.638
All right. I hear you.

09:28.668 --> 09:30.229
But I need for you to hear me.

09:30.259 --> 09:32.303
Marcel Girard is gonna be back

09:32.305 --> 09:33.174
to running things in
the Quarter soon enough.

09:33.204 --> 09:34.117
- (Crowd grumbles)
- I know. Listen.

09:34.147 --> 09:35.923
Now, I'm not asking you to trust Marcel,

09:35.925 --> 09:37.308
I'm asking you to trust me.

09:37.310 --> 09:39.844
Guys, what happens next, it's up to us.

09:39.846 --> 09:42.313
(Crowd murmuring)

09:44.288 --> 09:45.772
(Exhales)

09:45.802 --> 09:47.585
- Nice speech.
- Thank you.

09:48.186 --> 09:50.055
Except for the part about
the vampires and the witches.

09:50.057 --> 09:51.589
(Chuckles)

09:51.591 --> 09:53.508
Yeah, I still can't
believe all this is real.

09:53.510 --> 09:55.427
Well, you'll get used to that.

09:56.204 --> 09:57.846
Look, I saw something.

09:59.599 --> 10:00.932
Crime scene.

10:02.649 --> 10:04.569
I can't call it in.
I wouldn't even know how to.

10:05.033 --> 10:06.271
But I need you to come with me.

10:06.813 --> 10:08.940
- See for yourself. â€­
- Yeah.

10:10.071 --> 10:12.694
(Gasping)

10:13.697 --> 10:16.030
(Grunts)

10:19.970 --> 10:21.119
What did they do to you?

10:21.121 --> 10:22.587
Poison.

10:22.589 --> 10:23.872
(Groans)

10:23.874 --> 10:25.874
Let's get you out of here.

10:30.130 --> 10:31.629
(Both grunting)

10:37.521 --> 10:38.887
(Panting)

10:41.109 --> 10:42.023
Come on.

10:42.025 --> 10:43.274
Let's go.

10:45.478 --> 10:48.212
KINNEY: A neighbor
called in a disturbance.

10:51.484 --> 10:54.986
Someone was screaming bloody murder.

10:54.988 --> 10:57.922
I get in here, I don't know
whether to call a coroner

10:57.924 --> 11:00.124
or an exorcist.

11:01.728 --> 11:04.045
I mean, what the hell
am I looking at, Vincent?

11:04.047 --> 11:06.119
VINCENT: These are the Strix.

11:06.149 --> 11:07.932
Or what's left of them.

11:07.934 --> 11:09.450
Are they even human?

11:09.452 --> 11:11.436
No, these are far from human, Will.

11:12.074 --> 11:14.656
The guy who did this...

11:15.624 --> 11:17.659
some kind of vampire?

11:18.255 --> 11:19.694
This is not a normal vampire.

11:19.696 --> 11:21.412
(Screaming)

11:24.284 --> 11:25.917
(Grunts)

11:26.786 --> 11:28.836
(Gasping)

11:28.838 --> 11:31.372
(Groaning)

11:31.374 --> 11:33.541
Lie down. Don't move.

11:33.543 --> 11:35.593
(Panting)

11:36.202 --> 11:39.047
The prophecy is coming true.

11:39.049 --> 11:41.466
This is the day Lucien said would come.

11:44.039 --> 11:44.995
No.

11:45.717 --> 11:47.555
There has to be another way out of this.

11:48.401 --> 11:50.224
Especially with your magic.

11:53.446 --> 11:55.897
Here. Drink.

11:55.899 --> 11:57.619
It won't cure you,
but it will help you.

11:57.649 --> 11:58.388
(Moans)

11:58.418 --> 12:01.919
Now, Lucien has an antidote
to the poison in his penthouse.

12:01.921 --> 12:03.721
Even if I was cured,

12:03.723 --> 12:07.341
the power I used to fight
Lucien, it's gone.

12:08.595 --> 12:11.596
There's nothing that
can stop Marcel now.

12:13.266 --> 12:15.266
There might be one thing.

12:15.268 --> 12:17.268
Stay here. Watch Hope.

12:20.106 --> 12:22.607
I know you're hurt. I loved Davina, too.

12:23.777 --> 12:25.827
And it would break her
heart to see you like this.

12:25.829 --> 12:28.196
Don't mention her name.

12:28.198 --> 12:30.581
If it weren't for you,
she'd still be alive.

12:31.618 --> 12:32.583
But she's not.

12:32.585 --> 12:34.585
This is an insult to her memory.

12:34.587 --> 12:35.620
(Grunts)

12:35.622 --> 12:36.921
(Crowd clamoring)

12:38.458 --> 12:39.791
(Screams)

12:40.790 --> 12:41.709
Kol.

12:41.711 --> 12:42.960
(Neck cracks)

12:51.187 --> 12:52.804
(Clamoring continues)

12:55.525 --> 12:56.557
(Arm cracks)

12:56.559 --> 12:58.443
(Screams)

13:00.480 --> 13:01.979
(Panting)

13:03.733 --> 13:07.618
(Crowd cheering)

13:16.409 --> 13:17.792
Stop!

13:20.151 --> 13:21.021
Rebekah.

13:21.051 --> 13:22.216
Hayley has Hope and Freya.

13:22.218 --> 13:24.469
Take our brothers and go now.

13:24.871 --> 13:26.837
Marcel will not hurt me.

13:27.524 --> 13:30.074
Not if he knows what's good for him.

13:33.613 --> 13:35.330
(Groans)

13:38.769 --> 13:41.186
I've only got a short
while before I go mad.

13:42.188 --> 13:43.470
So your explanation

13:43.472 --> 13:45.973
better be quick and it better be good.

13:54.876 --> 13:58.743
(Grunting, panting)

14:00.530 --> 14:01.746
It's not here.

14:01.748 --> 14:03.202
- I can't find it. â€­
- Calm down.

14:03.232 --> 14:04.498
Freya, think.

14:04.938 --> 14:05.950
When you were poisoned before,

14:05.952 --> 14:07.284
Klaus stole an antidote from Lucien.

14:07.286 --> 14:08.452
It has to be here.

14:08.454 --> 14:10.487
There's no other place to look.

14:11.574 --> 14:13.484
If I can't find the cure,

14:13.514 --> 14:14.825
I will die.

14:14.827 --> 14:16.243
KLAUS: Freya!

14:16.245 --> 14:18.412
(Grunting, groaning)

14:24.642 --> 14:25.803
- Elijah... â€­
- Don't.

14:25.805 --> 14:26.971
Please.

14:26.973 --> 14:28.389
(Gasping)

14:28.391 --> 14:30.924
- We'll deal with it later.
- (Hope crying)

14:30.926 --> 14:32.092
I'm going to die.

14:32.094 --> 14:33.258
KLAUS: You're not going to die.

14:33.288 --> 14:34.544
(Chuckles)

14:34.574 --> 14:35.429
That sounds familiar!

14:35.431 --> 14:38.315
Isn't that what you
said to Finn and Cami?

14:39.997 --> 14:41.485
Look, Lucien engineered his venom

14:41.487 --> 14:43.169
from the seven werewolf packs,

14:43.199 --> 14:44.989
so maybe that's the key to a cure.

14:44.991 --> 14:47.107
Oh, great. That's the
first piece in a puzzle

14:47.109 --> 14:49.360
none of us will be alive to solve.

14:49.362 --> 14:50.661
I'm poisoned, Rebekah's hexed,

14:50.663 --> 14:51.983
and our brothers are bitten.

14:52.013 --> 14:53.947
We need three different cures
to three different ailments,

14:53.949 --> 14:55.449
each of which could take years to find,

14:55.451 --> 14:57.451
and none of us will
make it through the day.

15:00.790 --> 15:02.289
REBEKAH: Oh, that doesn't bode well.

15:03.053 --> 15:04.932
Let's cut the niceties.

15:05.370 --> 15:07.294
I need you to cure my brothers
before something's done

15:07.296 --> 15:08.407
that can't be undone.

15:08.437 --> 15:10.070
Oh, there's no going back.

15:10.100 --> 15:11.965
This is a fight to the death,

15:11.967 --> 15:13.183
and I won't lose.

15:13.185 --> 15:14.468
Why are you doing this?

15:14.470 --> 15:16.114
You really need to ask that?

15:16.144 --> 15:18.939
Can you honestly defend them?

15:18.941 --> 15:20.858
After what they did to me?

15:20.860 --> 15:21.814
To Davina?

15:21.844 --> 15:23.294
No.

15:23.446 --> 15:24.912
I cannot defend them.

15:24.914 --> 15:25.881
But they're my family,

15:25.911 --> 15:28.615
and I am begging you to cure them.

15:29.990 --> 15:32.252
There is no cure.

15:35.497 --> 15:37.257
What do you mean, there is no cure?

15:37.459 --> 15:39.409
Elijah is as good as dead.

15:39.411 --> 15:40.827
So is Kol.

15:42.047 --> 15:43.463
Before the night's over,

15:43.465 --> 15:46.212
Klaus will follow along with them.

15:46.585 --> 15:48.752
Who is your next victim?! Me?!

15:50.005 --> 15:52.089
No. No.

15:52.091 --> 15:55.058
Hey, I would never hurt you.

15:57.546 --> 15:59.880
But I'm not backing down.

15:59.882 --> 16:04.551
I am taking back my home,
my city, my freedom.

16:06.889 --> 16:09.264
The Marcel that I knew...

16:09.612 --> 16:12.790
the man that I loved...

16:12.820 --> 16:17.364
never fancied himself
judge, jury and executioner.

16:22.321 --> 16:23.537
(Sighs)

16:24.856 --> 16:26.806
You want justice?

16:28.114 --> 16:29.183
Well, that's a hell of a lot more

16:29.213 --> 16:31.561
than they ever offered me, but...

16:33.148 --> 16:34.564
sure.

16:34.566 --> 16:36.283
Sure.

16:39.612 --> 16:41.238
Let's have justice.

16:43.052 --> 16:44.326
(Gasping)

16:44.356 --> 16:45.492
You know, maybe it's fair

16:45.494 --> 16:48.144
that you and I pay for what
was done to Davina.

16:48.174 --> 16:49.389
â€­No.

16:49.746 --> 16:52.621
Davina didn't want revenge, okay?

16:52.651 --> 16:55.402
Just put me out of my misery!

16:55.404 --> 16:57.320
At least put me to bloody sleep!

16:57.322 --> 16:59.322
(Groans loudly)

17:00.203 --> 17:01.908
(Panting)

17:02.820 --> 17:04.327
KLAUS: Elijah, Hayley's
attending to Hope,

17:04.329 --> 17:06.329
but I can get her for you.

17:07.833 --> 17:10.250
She's struggling with it.

17:11.837 --> 17:14.170
Not our finest moment, Niklaus.

17:16.131 --> 17:17.176
No.

17:23.804 --> 17:26.278
Please take care of her.

17:27.532 --> 17:29.853
I promise you.

17:30.232 --> 17:32.105
And Rebekah.

17:32.107 --> 17:33.190
I will get

17:33.192 --> 17:35.546
our sister, and I will make Marcel pay.

17:35.576 --> 17:36.766
No, brother, no, no.

17:36.796 --> 17:39.446
This was not...

17:39.448 --> 17:40.530
(Inhales sharply)

17:40.532 --> 17:42.791
This was not Marcel.

17:42.821 --> 17:45.202
